---
title: Argentinian Bavette Steak with Roasted Veggies, Cheesy Bread & Chimichurri
description: Argentina is famous for its beef and magical, bright sauce: chimichurri—tangy, herbaceous, and a great complement to the earthy meat. This version is made with parsley, garlic, onion, vinegar, and chili powder, and is spooned over a bavette steak (so flavorful it’s called “the butcher’s cut”). On the side, as often seen on Argentine tables, cheese bread—ours a melty, toasty version—and a slew of garlicky roasted green beans, bell pepper, and red onion. ¡Olé!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/argentinian-bavette-steak-17836251.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/argentinian-bavette-steak-63694c4b84067de4e406e254-49c0615f.pdf
